{"t": "2026-04-27T15:42:31.301639+00:00", "iter": 17, "type": "tool", "name": "bash", "args": {"command": "cd /workspace/audit-repo && echo \"# DreamServer Audit Report\n\nThis repository contains a comprehensive audit of all 75 open pull requests against the DreamServer project.\n\n## Repository Structure\n\n- **/report/** - Executive summary, strategy, and contributor notes\n- **/prs/** - Detailed per-PR reviews with verdicts\n- **/testing/** - Test environments, hardware notes, and reproduction scripts\n- **/analysis/** - Dependency graph, risk matrix, and surface area analysis\n- **/research/** - Working notes, questions, and dead ends\n- **/decisions/** - ADR-style records for non-obvious choices\n- **/sources.md** - External content fetched with URLs and SHAs\n- **/tool-log.md** - Every tool call in order\n\n## How to Use This Report\n\n1. Start with `/report/executive-summary.md` for a 2-3 page synthesis\n2. Review `/analysis/dependency-graph.md` to understand PR interdependencies\n3. Check `/report/backlog-strategy.md` for recommended merge order\n4. For any PR, go to `/prs/pr-{number}/verdict.md` for the final decision\n5. Rerun tests using scripts in `/testing/reproductions/`\n\n## Audit Methodology\n\n- Every verdict is traceable to specific lines, tests, or architectural concerns\n- Code is run for every PR that changes testable paths\n- Risk scoring is explicit and documented in `/analysis/risk-matrix.md`\n- AMD GPU compatibility is explicitly checked due to partnership program\n- Bounty tier (Small/Medium/Large) is considered in verdicts\n\n## Key Findings\n\n- Total PRs: 75\n- Merge Now: [TBD]\n- Revise: [TBD]\n- Reject: [TBD]\n- Maintainer Judgment: [TBD]\n\n## Notes\n\n- This audit was performed on [DATE]\n- Baseline: main branch at commit [SHA]\n- GPU testing: [Hardware/VM details]\n\" > README.md"}, "wall_s": 0.07, "result_len": 457}
